   1	# Raya
   2	
   3	Raya is a minimal terminal chat agent powered by OpenRouter.
   4	
   5	Codename: Friday.
   6	
   7	## Quick Start
   8	
   9	```bash
  10	npm install
  11	cp .env.example .env
  12	```
  13	
  14	Add your OpenRouter API key to `.env`:
  15	
  16	```env
  17	OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
  18	OPENROUTER_MODEL=google/gemma-4-31b-it:free
  19	OPENROUTER_CONTEXT_TOKENS=128000
  20	RAYA_SEARCH_MAX_RESULTS=5
  21	RAYA_SEARCH_PAGE_CHARS=6000
  22	RAYA_SEARCH_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS=8000
  23	RAYA_IMAGE_MAX_DIMENSION=1280
  24	RAYA_IMAGE_JPEG_QUALITY=80
  25	RAYA_RETRY_ATTEMPTS=3
  26	RAYA_RETRY_INITIAL_DELAY_MS=1200
  27	```
  28	
  29	For global use from any directory, put the same values in `~/.raya/.env`:
  30	
  31	```bash
  32	mkdir -p ~/.raya
  33	cp .env.example ~/.raya/.env
  34	```
  35	
  36	Raya loads environment values in this order:
  37	
  38	1. `.env` in the current directory
  39	2. `~/.raya/.env`
  40	3. `.env` next to the installed package
  41	
  42	## Config
  43	
  44	Raya creates `~/.raya/config.json` automatically on first launch. You can also copy the example:
  45	
  46	```bash
  47	mkdir -p ~/.raya
  48	cp config.example.json ~/.raya/config.json
  49	```
  50	
  51	Config precedence:
  52	
  53	1. `~/.raya/config.json`
  54	2. `.raya/config.json` in the current workspace
  55	3. `raya.config.json` in the current workspace
  56	4. environment variables like `OPENROUTER_MODEL`
  57	
  58	Example:
  59	
  60	```json
  61	{
  62	  "model": "google/gemma-4-31b-it:free",
  63	  "models": [
  64	    "google/gemma-4-31b-it:free",
  65	    "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  66	    "anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet",
  67	    "google/gemini-2.0-flash-001"
  68	  ],
  69	  "mode": "Chat",
  70	  "contextTokens": 128000,
  71	  "search": {
  72	    "maxResults": 5,
  73	    "pageChars": 6000,
  74	    "fetchTimeoutMs": 8000
  75	  },
  76	  "images": {
  77	    "maxDimension": 1280,
  78	    "jpegQuality": 80
  79	  },
  80	  "retries": {
  81	    "maxAttempts": 3,
  82	    "initialDelayMs": 1200
  83	  },
  84	  "openrouter": {
  85	    "baseURL": "https://openrouter.ai/api/v1",
  86	    "referer": "https://github.com/haos/raya-agent",
  87	    "title": "Raya"
  88	  }
  89	}
  90	```
  91	
  92	Keep `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env` unless you explicitly want to store it in config.
  93	
  94	Run in development:
  95	
  96	```bash
  97	npm run dev
  98	```
  99	
 100	Build and run:
 101	
 102	```bash
 103	npm run build
 104	npm start
 105	```
 106	
 107	Install the local `raya` command:
 108	
 109	```bash
 110	npm link
 111	raya
 112	```
 113	
 114	## Commands
 115	
 116	- `/exit` - quit the chat
 117	- `/search query` - search the web, fetch linked pages, add page excerpts to the current context, and answer with sources
 118	- `/model` - open model picker
 119	- `/model model-id` - switch to a model directly
 120	
 121	Type `/` in interactive mode to see the command list.
 122	
 123	## Clipboard Images
 124	
 125	Copy an image on macOS, then paste it into Raya while writing a message:
 126	
 127	```text
 128	> what is on this screenshot? [Image 1]
 129	```
 130	
 131	Raya converts clipboard images to compressed JPEG, inserts placeholders like `[Image 1]`, `[Image 2]`, and sends them to the current OpenRouter model as multimodal input. The selected model must support images.
 132	
 133	Images are resized before sending to avoid oversized base64 payloads and reduce provider failures.
 134	
 135	## Web Context
 136	
 137	`/search` is current-session context, not long-term memory. Raya searches the web, opens the top result pages, extracts text excerpts, and inserts those excerpts into the model context for the current conversation.
 138	
 139	Raya also auto-searches when the message clearly asks for current or web-dependent information, for example latest news, current prices, weather, recent releases, or explicit requests like “найди”, “поищи”, “посмотри в интернете”.
 140	
 141	If a page blocks fetching or returns unsupported content, Raya marks it as `snippet only` and uses the search snippet as a weak fallback.
 142	
 143	## Runtime Stats
 144	
 145	After each answer Raya prints approximate runtime stats:
 146	
 147	```text
 148	stats › 18.4 tok/s · context 2.1k/128.0k (1.6%) · answer 420 tokens
 149	```
 150	
 151	Token counts are estimated locally, so they are useful for tracking context pressure, answer size, and speed, not exact billing.
